Yes you can have `ArrayList`s as a keys in a hash map, but it is a **very bad idea** since they are **mutable**.

If you change the `ArrayList` in any way (or any of its elements), the mapping will basically be lost, since the key won&#39;t have the same `hashCode` as it had when it was inserted.

The rule of thumb is to use only immutable data types as keys in a hash map. As suggested by Alex Stybaev, you probably want to create a `Bigram` class like this:

